# desk-break (Cursor rule)

macOS-only movement-break reminder: a `launchd` agent runs a config-driven shell
script on an interval, shows a localized reminder, optionally plays `music-cli`
music, and tracks a streak. See `AGENTS.md` (repo root) for install/run details and
`plugins/desk-break/skills/desk-break/SKILL.md` for the full config reference.

## Rules when editing

- **Single source of truth**: all logic lives in
  `plugins/desk-break/skills/desk-break/reminder.sh`. Don't duplicate it; other
  entry points call it.
- **i18n**: user-facing text, exercise cards, and copy live in
  `plugins/desk-break/skills/desk-break/i18n/<lang>/{moves.txt,phrases.txt,strings.env}`.
  Add strings to `strings.env` (both `en` and `zh`), never hardcode UI text in the script.
- **AppleScript**: pass text via `osascript ... on run argv` (UTF-8 safe). Never use
  env vars + `system attribute` (it garbles Chinese/emoji).
- **macOS only**: depends on `launchd`, `ioreg` (HIDIdleTime), `osascript`, `say`.
- **No secrets** in `config.env` or scripts.

## Common commands

```bash
~/.local/bin/desk-break.sh --test
~/.local/bin/desk-break.sh --stats
~/.local/bin/desk-break.sh --report "what went wrong"
```
